          Bodum: From the Soul of Slow Coffee.

          Bodum Brazil French Press Coffee Maker

          Attractive and functional design. Made in Europe.

          The French press coffee maker is the simplest of all brewing systems, where coarsely ground beans meet hot water right off the boil. The right temperature (9296 C, 195205 F) brings the optimal extraction power for the essential oils in the beans to develop their full flavor profile in just four minutes. An easy press on the plunger locks the grinds at the bottom of the glass carafe and stops the brewing process.

          • Body, handle, & lid made of BPA free plastic
          • Beaker is made of heat resistant borosilicate glass
          • Filter & plunger is made of stainless steel
          • Brews & makes delicious coffee
          • Made in Europe

          How to brew French press coffee:

          Step 1

          For each 4-ounces of coffee, put 1 rounded tablespoon or 1 Bodum scoop of coarse-ground coffee into the pot.

          Step 2

          Pour hot (not boiling) water into the pot. Leave a minimum of 1 inch of space at the top. Stir with a plastic spoon.

          Step 3

          Place the plunger unit on top of the pot. Do not press down. Let the coffee brew for 4 minutes.

          Step 4

          After 4 minutes press down the plunger and enjoy.

          Bodum quality in every component.

          Borosilicate Glass beaker

          The beaker is made of High-Quality Borosilicate glass is ultra-light and strong, has great heat- resistant properties, and will not get cloudy in the dishwasher.

          Spiral plate

          The Stainless Steel spiral plate keeps the filter mesh in place and makes sure that water goes through but no ground coffee. The flexible spiral provides a universal fit taking into account the manufacturing tolerances of glass jugs.

          Mesh

          The Stainless Steel filter mesh is a key component to the Bodum coffee makers. It separates the ground coffee beans from the water after the brewing has stopped.

          Cross plate

          The Stainless Steel cross plate holds the mesh in place together with the spiral plate.

          Product Description

          About the BRAZIL French Press Coffee Maker Savor perfectly brewed coffee every day with the BRAZIL French press coffee maker. Part of Bodums iconic French press brewing range, this superb coffee maker has certainly stood the test of time; its been brewing seriously good coffee since the 1980s. Like other products in our French press range, the BRAZIL coffee maker uses premium quality borosilicate glass for the carafe and a reusable stainless steel filter to extract the full flavor from your precious beans. However its lightweight, BPA-free plastic body, handle and lid look stylish while epitomizing our motto that good design doesnt have to be expensive. Combining affordable design with a simple, environmentally friendly brewing system, the BRAZIL French press coffee maker offers everybody the chance to appreciate one of lifes great pleasures: a delicious cup of joe! Main Features & Benefits

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          • Blooming Coffee
            4.0 out of 5 stars Small and efficient
            Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
            Size: 12 ozColor: BlackVerified Purchase
            The Bodum Brazil 12-ounce French press is known for its elegant design and functionality. One of its strengths is its generous 12-ounce capacity, making it an ideal choice for brewing larger quantities of coffee.

            On the positive side, its heat-resistant borosilicate glass construction ensures durability and the ability to observe the coffee brewing process. Additionally, the ergonomic handle and stainless steel base offer a comfortable grip and solid stability.

            Ease of use is another strong point. The pressing system is efficient, providing flavorful and well-filtered coffee. Cleaning is also straightforward, as all parts are detachable and dishwasher-safe.

            However, some users have noted certain drawbacks. Some may find the glass thinner than expected, potentially making it more prone to breakage if not handled with care. Furthermore, the lack of a double-wall system could impact its ability to retain coffee temperature for an extended period.

            In summary, the Bodum Brazil 34-ounce French press is an attractive option for those seeking a coffee maker with the capacity to brew multiple cups simultaneously. Its stylish design and user-friendly features are positive aspects, although some users might prefer thicker glass for enhanced durability and improved heat retention.
